<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-09-25T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-09-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9–2546: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-09-25T18:00:00-04:00">September
                                    25, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>788. For General Marshall. Thank you for information contained in your
                                1556.<note n="65" xml:id="d584fn65">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> As you know by now the Soviet
                            proposal was defeated in the Security Council yesterday by vote of 7 to
                            2 but I want to let you know that the advice you gave the Chinese was in
                            full accord with the views of the State Department. With best
                            regards.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Clayton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>